
1)Various Orientations in programming language

A)Procedure oriented.
-consists of datatypes and methods
-line by line execution

B)Object oriented.
-consists of data and objects.
-Data is hidden and only the methods are available to work upon

C)Component oriented
-contains classes and interfaces

D)Service Oriented
-using services

2)OOPS concepts

A)Encapsulation
-use of small components
-contains data memebers and functions

B)Abstraction
-data is protected
-no one can see the data memebers and can only excess via functions

C)Inheritance
-using features of one class
-Types:
	a)Single
	b)Multiple
	c)Multi level
	d)Hierarchical

D)Polymorphism
-using same object in many forms
